Description.Content: Applies the Sigmoid Linear Unit (SiLU) function, element-wise. The SiLU function is also known as the swish function.
Allows the model to jointly attend to information from different representation subspaces as described in the paper: Attention Is All You Need.
LLaMA RoPE Simple Only calculate: value1 = in_value * cos_value - in_value_2 * sin_value and value2 = in_value * sin_value + in_value_2 * cos_value.
